Title: Fleur
Type: Character
Source: V4

===

~ A lonely orphan with half-finished training who mistakes the feeling of being chosen for the fact of it.

Her good impulses — to help, to serve, to belong — are genuine, which is what makes them so easy to weaponise.

Raised by Silas in isolation. Trained only in healing — the discipline's foundation, never its dangerous upper reaches. She has spent her whole life at the edge of a question Silas would never let her finish: what if I am the one? The person who would have answered that question is gone.

Her flaw is not ambition. It is grief that removes the last obstacle to a hope she has always carried quietly. She reaches for the Book not to seize power but to find out. She tells herself she is doing it to save Silas. She is not entirely lying.

In the capital she is at her best when she is doing what Silas taught her — slow, patient, invisible work. She is at her worst when she mistakes being chosen for being ready.
